  "target_response": {
    "text": "You don't have to give it up — timing and dose are the levers. Caffeine hangs around: its half-life is roughly 5 to 6 hours, so the coffee you drink at 5pm before a 6pm session still leaves a meaningful fraction circulating at your 11:15pm bedtime. Your sleep is holding up so far — 415 minutes last night with a weekly average of 428 minutes — so this is prevention rather than repair. Two options to test: shift the coffee a couple of hours earlier in the afternoon and let the tail effect carry you into the session, or halve the dose from your usual 180 mg and see whether the workout still feels good. If your nights start shortening or fragmenting, tighten the cutoff further. Caffeine before training is a legitimate, well-studied aid — this is tuning, not quitting.",
